The paper discusses a new selection scheme for cellular Genetic Algorithms (cGA) to enhance diversity and control selective pressure. This falls under the category of Evolutionary Computation (cs.NE) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the trade-off between cGA and island models, which involves parallel computing and distributed systems, falling under the categories of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed scheme on a well-known optimization problem, which involves measuring diversity and performance, falling under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG).
